OL,6,FChildren who contract the disease can
OL,7,Fbecome very unwell. It can lead to
OL,8,Fhospitalisation and even death in some
OL,9,Frare cases.
OL,11,FPeople who are at-risk include babies
OL,12,Fand young children, pregnant women and
OL,13,Fpeople with weakened immunity.
OL,15,FMMR is part of the Routine Childhood
OL,16,FImmunisation Programme ` with one dose
OL,17,Foffered when a child is one-year-old
OL,18,Fand another second dose at three-years
OL,19,Fand four-months.
